   <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="discussion">
      <p>
Remarks
</p>
      <p>
         <tp:taxon-name>
Campanulina denticulata
</tp:taxon-name>
was considered a synonym of 
<tp:taxon-name>
Earleria panicula
(G.O. Sars, 1874)
</tp:taxon-name>
by several authors (
Leloup 1974
; 
Schuchert 2003
), but 
Calder (2012)
suggested that the Atlantic 
<tp:taxon-name>
E. panicula
</tp:taxon-name>
is a different species from the Indo-Pacific 
<tp:taxon-name>
C. denticulata
</tp:taxon-name>
. The comparison of the material from the Valdivia Seamount with colonies of 
<tp:taxon-name>
E. panicula
</tp:taxon-name>
collected in NW Africa showed some morphological differences, and agrees with descriptions of 
<tp:taxon-name>
C. denticulata
</tp:taxon-name>
given by 
Clarke (1907)
and 
Vervoort (1966)
.
</p>
